Weather App

Description
A simple weather app that allows users to check the current weather for a specific city. The app uses the OpenWeatherMap API to fetch weather data.

Features
- Displays the current temperature and weather description.
- Allows users to search for the weather in different cities.
- Converts temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit.
- Auto-updates weather every minute.

Getting Started
1. Clone the repository to your local machine.

Usage
1. Enter the city name in the search bar.
2. Click the "Search" button to view the weather for the specified city.
3. The weather information will be displayed, including temperature and weather description.
4. The temperature is initially displayed in Celsius; click the "Convert to Fahrenheit" button to convert.

Files
- `index.html`: The main HTML file for the application.
- `styles.css`: The stylesheet for styling the HTML elements.
- `index.js`: The JavaScript file containing the logic for fetching and displaying weather data.

Languages Technologies Used
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- OpenWeatherMap API

Sources
- Weather data provided by OpenWeatherMap (https://openweathermap.org/).
- Icons from Font Awesome (https://fontawesome.com/).